upsEIdentityAttachedDevices.name: upsEIdentityAttachedDevices

upsESystemFaultCode.description: The fault code of UPS.Please refer the fault code of 'Q6' for details.

upsESystemConfigInputVoltage.name: upsESystemConfigInputVoltage
upsESystemConfigInputVoltage.description: The magnitude of the nominal input voltage presented in 0.1 V. On those systems which support read-write access to this object, if there is an attempt to set this variable to a value that is not supported, the request must be rejected and the agent shall respond with an appropriate error message, i.e., badValue for SNMPv1, or inconsistentValue for SNMPv2.

upsESystemConfigInputFrequence.name: upsESystemConfigInputFrequence
upsESystemConfigInputFrequence.description: The nominal input frequency presented in 0.1 Hz. On those systems which support read-write access to this object, if there is an attempt to set this variable to a value that is not supported, the request must be rejected and the agent shall respond with an appropriate error message, i.e., badValue for SNMPv1, or inconsistentValue for SNMPv2.

upsESystemConfigOutputVoltage.name: upsESystemConfigOutputVoltage
upsESystemConfigOutputVoltage.description: The magnitude of the nominal output voltage presented in 0.1V. On those systems which support read-write access to this object, if there is an attempt to set this variable to a value that is not supported, the request must be rejected and the agent shall respond with an appropriate error message, i.e., badValue for SNMPv1, or inconsistentValue for SNMPv2

upsESystemConfigOutputFrequency.name: upsESystemConfigOutputFrequency
upsESystemConfigOutputFrequency.description: The nominal output frequency presented in 0.1Hz. On those systems which support read-write access to this object, if there is an attempt to set this variable to a value that is not supported, the request must be rejected and the agent shall respond with an appropriate error message, i.e., badValue for SNMPv1, or inconsistentValue for SNMPv2.

upsESystemConfigOutputPower.name: upsESystemConfigOutputPower

upsESystemConfigOutputLoadHighSetPoint.name: upsESystemConfigOutputLoadHighSetPoint

upsESystemConfigOverTemperatureSetPoint.name: upsESystemConfigOverTemperatureSetPoint
upsESystemConfigOverTemperatureSetPoint.description: The maximum temperature allowed before the UPS operation temperature is too high, presented in 0.1 degree.

upsESystemInputSourceNum.description: The present external source of input power.

upsESystemInputLineBads.name: upsESystemInputLineBads

upsESystemInputCurrent.description: The measured input mandatory from the UPS meters in 0.1 amps.

upsESystemInputWatts.description: The measured input real power in watts.

upsESystemOutputNumPhase.name: upsESystemOutputNumPhase
upsESystemOutputNumPhase.description: The number of metered output phases, serves as the table index. This value indicate the device initialized feature.

upsESystemOutputTable.name: upsESystemOutputTable
upsESystemOutputTable.description: A list of output table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of upsESystemOutputNumPhase.

upsESystemOutputEntry.name: upsESystemOutputEntry
upsESystemOutputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular line.

upsESystemOutputPhase.name: upsESystemOutputPhase
upsESystemOutputPhase.description: The number of the phase. Serves as index for output table

upsESystemOutputVoltage.description: The measured output voltage from the UPS meters in 0.1 volts

upsESystemOutputLoad.name: upsESystemOutputLoad
upsESystemOutputLoad.description: The UPS output load in percent of rated capacity.

upsESystemBypassNumPhase.name: upsESystemBypassNumPhase
upsESystemBypassNumPhase.description: The number of bypass phases, serves as the table index. This value indicate the device initialized feature

upsESystemBypassTable.description: A list of bypass table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of upsESystemBypassNumPhase.

upsESystemBypassEntry.name: upsESystemBypassEntry
upsESystemBypassEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular line.

upsESystemBypassPhase.name: upsESystemBypassPhase
upsESystemBypassPhase.description: The number of the phase. Serves as index for bypass table

upsESystemBypassFrequency.name: upsESystemBypassFrequency
upsESystemBypassFrequency.description: The measured bypass frequency from the UPS meters in 0.1 Hz.

upsESystemBypassVoltage.name: upsESystemBypassVoltage
upsESystemBypassVoltage.description: The measured bypass voltage from the UPS meters in 0.1 volts

upsESystemBypassCurrent.name: upsESystemBypassCurrent
upsESystemBypassCurrent.description: The measured bypass mandatory from the UPS meters in 0.1 amps

upsESystemBypassWatts.name: upsESystemBypassWatts
upsESystemBypassWatts.description: The measured input real power in watts.

upsESystemConfigBelowCapacityLimit.name: upsESystemConfigBelowCapacityLimit
upsESystemConfigBelowCapacityLimit.description: The UPS batteries capacity(%) limit for shutdown

upsESystemConfigBelowRemainTimeLimit.name: upsESystemConfigBelowRemainTimeLimit
upsESystemConfigBelowRemainTimeLimit.description: The UPS batteries backup time(minute) limit for shutdown

upsEBatteryStatus.name: upsEBatteryStatus
upsEBatteryStatus.description: The status of UPS battery, a value of batteryLow indicates that the battery-low status bit has been set from device. A value of batteryDepleted indicates that the UPS will be unable to sustain the present load when and if the utility power is lost (including the possibility that the utility power is mandatoryly absent and the UPS is unable to sustain the output)

upsESecondsOnBattery.name: upsESecondsOnBattery
upsESecondsOnBattery.description: If the unit is on battery power, the elapsed time since the UPS last switched to battery power, or the time since the network management subsystem was last restarted, whichever is less. 0 shall be returned if the unit is not on battery power

upsEBatteryEstimatedMinutesRemaining.name: upsEBatteryEstimatedMinutesRemaining
upsEBatteryEstimatedMinutesRemaining.description: An estimate of the time to battery charge depletion under the present load conditions if the utility power is off and remains off, or if it were to be lost and remain off.

upsEBatteryEstimatedChargeRemaining.name: upsEBatteryEstimatedChargeRemaining
upsEBatteryEstimatedChargeRemaining.description: An estimate of the battery charge remaining expressed as a percent of full charge

upsEPositiveBatteryVoltage.name: upsEPositiveBatteryVoltage
upsEPositiveBatteryVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present positive battery voltage in 0.1 Volt DC

upsENegativeBatteryVoltage.name: upsENegativeBatteryVoltage
upsENegativeBatteryVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present negative battery voltage in 0.1 Volt DC

upsEBatteryCellNumber.name: upsEBatteryCellNumber
upsEBatteryCellNumber.description: This object indicate the cell number of each set.

upsEBatteryTemperature.name: upsEBatteryTemperature
upsEBatteryTemperature.description: The ambient temperature at or near the UPS Battery casing in 0.1 degree.

upsEBatteryLastReplacedDate.name: upsEBatteryLastReplacedDate
upsEBatteryLastReplacedDate.description: The date when the Batteries in this UPS were last replaced. The format should be DD/MM/YYYY.

upsEChargerModulesNum.name: upsEChargerModulesNum
upsEChargerModulesNum.description: The number of charger modules inserted to UPS systems. served as the index of the upsEChargerModulesTable. The default value 0 indicate that the UPS system don't have separate charger module.

upsEChargerModulesTable.name: upsEChargerModulesTable
upsEChargerModulesTable.description: A list of charger modules entries. The number of entries is given by the value of upsEchargerModulesNum.

upsEChargerModulesEntry.name: upsEChargerModulesEntry
upsEChargerModulesEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular charger module.

chargerModulesNum.name: chargerModulesNum
chargerModulesNum.description: The number of charger modules. Serves as index for charger module table

positiveChargeVotlage.name: positiveChargeVotlage
positiveChargeVotlage.description: The measured positive charger voltage from the UPS meters in 0.1 volts

negativeChargeVoltage.name: negativeChargeVoltage
negativeChargeVoltage.description: The measured nepositive charger voltage from the UPS meters in 0.1 volts

positiveChargeCurrent.name: positiveChargeCurrent
positiveChargeCurrent.description: The measured positive charger mandatory from the UPS meters in in 0.1 amps.

negativeChargeCurrent.name: negativeChargeCurrent
negativeChargeCurrent.description: The measured nepositive charger mandatory from the UPS meters in 0.1 amps.

chargerModulesTemperature.name: chargerModulesTemperature
chargerModulesTemperature.description: The measured charger temperature from the UPS meters in 0.1 degree.

chargerModulesMode.name: chargerModulesMode
chargerModulesMode.description: The working mode of charger modules.

upsEUPSModulesNum.name: upsEUPSModulesNum
upsEUPSModulesNum.description: The number of UPS modules inserted to UPS systems. served as the index of the upsEModulesTable. the default value 0 indicate that the UPS system do not have separate UPS module.

upsEModulesTable.description: A list of UPS modules entries. The number of entries is given by the value of upsEModulesNum.

upsEModulesNum.description: The number of UPS modules. Serves as index for UPS module table

upsEModulePositiveBusVolt.description: The measured positive upsE module voltage from the UPS meters in 0.1 volts

upsEModuleNegativeBusVolt.name: upsEModuleNegativeBusVolt
upsEModuleNegativeBusVolt.description: The measured nepositive upsE module voltage from the UPS meters in 0.1 volts

upsEModuleTemperature.name: upsEModuleTemperature
upsEModuleTemperature.description: The measured upsE module temperature from the UPS meters in 0.1 degree.

upsEModuleWorkingMode.name: upsEModuleWorkingMode
upsEModuleWorkingMode.description: The working mode of UPS modules.

upsEModuleOutputCurrentR.name: upsEModuleOutputCurrentR
upsEModuleOutputCurrentR.description: The measured upsE module output mandatory from the UPS meters in 0.1 A.

upsEModuleOutputWattR.name: upsEModuleOutputWattR
upsEModuleOutputWattR.description: The measured upsE module output watts from the UPS meters in watts.

upsEModuleOutputLoadR.name: upsEModuleOutputLoadR
upsEModuleOutputLoadR.description: The output load of UPS modules in %.

upsEModuleWarningCode.name: upsEModuleWarningCode
upsEModuleWarningCode.description: The warning code of ups modules.Please refer the warning table of 'QU,XX' for details.

upsEModuleFaultCode.name: upsEModuleFaultCode
upsEModuleFaultCode.description: The fault code of ups modules.Please refer command 'QU,XX' for details.

upsEModuleTrapState.name: upsEModuleTrapState
upsEModuleTrapState.description: the values indicate the unrestored traps. For example, after AC fail, so the value of upsETrapState should be '1'. And then the AC restore, the value of upsEModuleTrapState should change to empty.

upsEModuleConfigOutputVA.name: upsEModuleConfigOutputVA
upsEModuleConfigOutputVA.description: The magnitude of the nominal Volt-Amp rating presented in VA.

upsEModuleOutputCurrentT.description: The measured upsE module output mandatory from the UPS meters in 0.1 A.

upsEModuleOutputWattS.description: The measured upsE module output watts from the UPS meters in watts.

upsEModuleOutputWattT.description: The measured upsE module output watts from the UPS meters in watts.

upsEModuleOutputLoadS.name: upsEModuleOutputLoadS

upsEModuleOutputLoadT.name: upsEModuleOutputLoadT
upsEModuleOutputLoadT.description: The output load of UPS modules in %.

upsEModuleOutputVAR.name: upsEModuleOutputVAR
upsEModuleOutputVAR.description: The magnitude of the nominal Volt-Amp rating presented in VA.

upsEModuleOutputVAS.name: upsEModuleOutputVAS
upsEModuleOutputVAS.description: The magnitude of the nominal Volt-Amp rating presented in VA.

upsEModuleOutputVAT.name: upsEModuleOutputVAT
upsEModuleOutputVAT.description: The magnitude of the nominal Volt-Amp rating presented in VA.

upsELoadSegment1OffDelay.name: upsELoadSegment1OffDelay
upsELoadSegment1OffDelay.description: Setting this object will shutdown the UPS Load Segment output after the indicated number of seconds, or less. Setting this object to 0 will cause the shutdown to occur immediately. Setting this object to -1 will abort the countdown. Read this object will get countdown value of the Load Segment.

upsELoadSegment1OnDelay.name: upsELoadSegment1OnDelay
upsELoadSegment1OnDelay.description: Setting this object will start the Load segment output after the indicated number of seconds, including starting the UPS, if necessary. Setting this object to 0 will cause the startup to occur immediately. Setting this object to -1 will abort the countdown.

upsELoadSegment1AutoOffTimer.name: upsELoadSegment1AutoOffTimer
upsELoadSegment1AutoOffTimer.description: The load segment turns automatically off after the delay while the unit operates on battery, but the shutdown is cancelled if the utility return before the delay has expired.

upsELoadSegment1AutoOnTimer.name: upsELoadSegment1AutoOnTimer
upsELoadSegment1AutoOnTimer.description: The load segment is automatically turned on after a selected delay if it has been shutdown due to on battery.

upsELoadSegment2OffDelay.name: upsELoadSegment2OffDelay
upsELoadSegment2OffDelay.description: Setting this object will shutdown the UPS Load Segment output after the indicated number of seconds, or less. Setting this object to 0 will cause the shutdown to occur immediately. Setting this object to -1 will abort the countdown. Read this object will get countdown value of the Load Segment.

upsELoadSegment2OnDelay.name: upsELoadSegment2OnDelay
upsELoadSegment2OnDelay.description: Setting this object will start the Load segment output after the indicated number of seconds, including starting the UPS, if necessary. Setting this object to 0 will cause the startup to occur immediately. Setting this object to -1 will abort the countdown.

upsELoadSegment2AutoOffTimer.name: upsELoadSegment2AutoOffTimer
upsELoadSegment2AutoOffTimer.description: The load segment turns automatically off after the delay while the unit operates on battery, but the shutdown is cancelled if the utility return before the delay has expired.

upsELoadSegment2AutoOnTimer.name: upsELoadSegment2AutoOnTimer
upsELoadSegment2AutoOnTimer.description: The load segment is automatically turned on after a selected delay if it has been shutdown due to on battery.

upsEEnvironmentCurrentTemperature.name: upsEEnvironmentCurrentTemperature
upsEEnvironmentCurrentTemperature.description: The measurement of temperature sensor, in 0.1 degree

upsEEnvironmentTemperatureHighSetPoint.name: upsEEnvironmentTemperatureHighSetPoint
upsEEnvironmentTemperatureHighSetPoint.description: The set point for high temperature warning, in 0.1 degrees. This value must be greater than upsEEnvironmentTemperatureLowSetPoint, and the least significant digit must be zero.

upsEEnvironmentTemperatureHighStatus.name: upsEEnvironmentTemperatureHighStatus
upsEEnvironmentTemperatureHighStatus.description: To enable/disable high set point check with sensor temperature.

upsEEnvironmentTemperatureLowSetPoint.name: upsEEnvironmentTemperatureLowSetPoint
upsEEnvironmentTemperatureLowSetPoint.description: The set point for low temperature warning, in 0.1 degrees. This value must be less than upsEEnvironmentTemperatureHighSetPoint, and the least significant digit must be zero.

upsEEnvironmentTemperatureLowStatus.name: upsEEnvironmentTemperatureLowStatus
upsEEnvironmentTemperatureLowStatus.description: To enable/disable low set point check with sensor temperature.

upsEEnvironmentTemperatureOffset.name: upsEEnvironmentTemperatureOffset
upsEEnvironmentTemperatureOffset.description: The offset to calibrate temperature of EMD, in 0.1 degrees

upsEEnvironmentCurrentHumidity.name: upsEEnvironmentCurrentHumidity
upsEEnvironmentCurrentHumidity.description: The measurement of sensor humidity present in %.

upsEEnvironmentHumidityHighSetPoint.name: upsEEnvironmentHumidityHighSetPoint
upsEEnvironmentHumidityHighSetPoint.description: The set point for high humidity warning, in %. This value must be greater than upsEEnvironmentHumidityLowSetPoint.

upsEEnvironmentHumidityHighStatus.name: upsEEnvironmentHumidityHighStatus
upsEEnvironmentHumidityHighStatus.description: To enable/disable high set point check with emd humidity.

upsEEnvironmentHumidityLowSetPoint.name: upsEEnvironmentHumidityLowSetPoint
upsEEnvironmentHumidityLowSetPoint.description: The set point for low humidity warning, in %. This value must be less than upsEEnvironmentHumidityHighSetPoint.

upsEEnvironmentHumidityLowStatus.name: upsEEnvironmentHumidityLowStatus
upsEEnvironmentHumidityLowStatus.description: To enable/disable high set point check with emd humidity.

upsEEnvironmentHumidityOffset.name: upsEEnvironmentHumidityOffset
upsEEnvironmentHumidityOffset.description: The offset to calibrate humidity of EMD, in %.

upsEEnvironmentContactsNum.name: upsEEnvironmentContactsNum
upsEEnvironmentContactsNum.description: The number of environment contacts, serves as the table index.

upsEEnvironmentContactTable.name: upsEEnvironmentContactTable
upsEEnvironmentContactTable.description: A list of contacts table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of upsEEnvironmentContactsNum

upsEEnvironmentContactEntry.name: upsEEnvironmentContactEntry
upsEEnvironmentContactEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular contact

upsEEnvironmentContactIndex.name: upsEEnvironmentContactIndex
upsEEnvironmentContactIndex.description: The number of environment contacts. Serves as index for environment contact table

upsEBatteryTestStart.name: upsEBatteryTestStart
upsEBatteryTestStart.description: This object specify the battery test type and initiate battery test. If battTestWithTime selected, the test time is refer to upsEBatteryTestSettingTime.

upsEBatteryTestSettingTime.name: upsEBatteryTestSettingTime
upsEBatteryTestSettingTime.description: The object specify the test time for battery test in seconds.

upsEBatteryTestResult.name: upsEBatteryTestResult
upsEBatteryTestResult.description: This object indicate the test result of battery.

upsEBatteryTestStartTime.name: upsEBatteryTestStartTime
upsEBatteryTestStartTime.description: The value of the time the test in progress was initiated, or, if no test is in progress, the time the previous test was initiated. If the value of upsETestBatteryTestResult is noTestsInitiated(6), upsETestStartTime has the value 01/01/1970 00:00:00.

upsEBatteryTestElapsedTime.name: upsEBatteryTestElapsedTime
upsEBatteryTestElapsedTime.description: The amount of time in format hh:mm:ss, since the test in progress was initiated, or, if no test is in progress, the previous test took to complete. If the value of upsTestResultsSummary is idle(1), upsTestElapsedTime has the value 00:00:00.

upsEBatteryTestScheduleTable.name: upsEBatteryTestScheduleTable
upsEBatteryTestScheduleTable.description: This table describes the schedule for automatically battery test.

upsEBatteryTestScheduleEntry.name: upsEBatteryTestScheduleEntry
upsEBatteryTestScheduleEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to schedule test.

upsEBatteryTestScheduleIndex.name: upsEBatteryTestScheduleIndex
upsEBatteryTestScheduleIndex.description: The index of battery test scheduled.

upsEBatteryTestScheduleDay.name: upsEBatteryTestScheduleDay
upsEBatteryTestScheduleDay.description: The weekday or specaial day on which the UPS should start battery test.

upsEBatteryTestScheduleTime.name: upsEBatteryTestScheduleTime
upsEBatteryTestScheduleTime.description: The time that the battery test will be initiated in hh:mm format.

upsEBatteryTestScheduleTestWithTime.name: upsEBatteryTestScheduleTestWithTime
upsEBatteryTestScheduleTestWithTime.description: The battery time of setting time test in seconds.

upsEBatteryTestScheduleSpecialDay.name: upsEBatteryTestScheduleSpecialDay
upsEBatteryTestScheduleSpecialDay.description: The special day that the battery test will be initiated in dd/mm/yyyy format.

upsEControlOutputOffDelay.name: upsEControlOutputOffDelay
upsEControlOutputOffDelay.description: Setting this value to other than zero will cause the UPS output to turn off after the number of seconds.

upsEControlOutputOnDelay.name: upsEControlOutputOnDelay
upsEControlOutputOnDelay.description: Setting this value to other than zero will cause the UPS output to turn on after the number of seconds.

upsEControlOutputOnOffControl.name: upsEControlOutputOnOffControl
upsEControlOutputOnOffControl.description: upsEOutputOff ( 1 ) indicates the shutdown sequence, upsEOutputOffCancel ( 2 ) indicates cancel the shutdown sequence, upsESleep( 3 ) indicates shutdown UPS first, then switch on.

upsEShutdownEventsTable.name: upsEShutdownEventsTable
upsEShutdownEventsTable.description: This table describes the parametes for shutdown process when shutdown event occurs

upsEShutdownEventsEntry.name: upsEShutdownEventsEntry
upsEShutdownEventsEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular shutdown event line

upsEShutdownEventAction.name: upsEShutdownEventAction
upsEShutdownEventAction.description: Status of the corresponding shutdown Event. When set to disable(), shutdown process will not start when corresponding event occured.

upsEShutdownwarningPeriodTime.name: upsEShutdownwarningPeriodTime
upsEShutdownwarningPeriodTime.description: The Delay in seconds after the occurance of the curresponding shutdown event, and warning message should be popped in this period.

upsEShutdownWarningPeriodInterval.name: upsEShutdownWarningPeriodInterval
upsEShutdownWarningPeriodInterval.description: The frequency of sending warning messages to the connected clients when the curresponding shutdown event occurs. The value is in units of seconds.

upsEControlWeeklyScheduleTable.name: upsEControlWeeklyScheduleTable
upsEControlWeeklyScheduleTable.description: The table to schedule shutting down the ups by weekly

upsEControlWeeklyScheduleEntry.name: upsEControlWeeklyScheduleEntry
upsEControlWeeklyScheduleEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular line

upsEWeeklyScheduleShutdownDay.name: upsEWeeklyScheduleShutdownDay
upsEWeeklyScheduleShutdownDay.description: the weekday on which upsE shoud shutdown

upsEWeeklyScheduleShutdownTime.name: upsEWeeklyScheduleShutdownTime
upsEWeeklyScheduleShutdownTime.description: The time that the process of shutting down the UPS will be initiated in hh:mm format.

upsEWeeklyScheduleRestartDay.name: upsEWeeklyScheduleRestartDay
upsEWeeklyScheduleRestartDay.description: the weekday on which the UPS should restart.

upsEWeeklyScheduleRestartTime.name: upsEWeeklyScheduleRestartTime
upsEWeeklyScheduleRestartTime.description: The time the UPS will restart in hh:mm format.

upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleTable.name: upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleTable
upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleTable.description: The table to schedule shutting down the ups.

upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleEntry.name: upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleEntry
upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular line.

upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleIndex.name: upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleIndex
upsEControlSpecialDayScheduleIndex.description: The index of special day schedule.

upsESpecialDayScheduleShutdownDay.name: upsESpecialDayScheduleShutdownDay
upsESpecialDayScheduleShutdownDay.description: The special day on which UPS should shutdown with the format of DD/MM/YYYY.

upsESpecialDayScheduleShutdownTime.name: upsESpecialDayScheduleShutdownTime
upsESpecialDayScheduleShutdownTime.description: The time that the process of shutting down the UPS will be initiated in hh:mm format.

upsESpecialDayScheduleRestartDay.name: upsESpecialDayScheduleRestartDay
upsESpecialDayScheduleRestartDay.description: The special day on which the UPS should restart with the format of DD/MM/YYYY.

upsESpecialDayScheduleRestartTime.name: upsESpecialDayScheduleRestartTime
upsESpecialDayScheduleRestartTime.description: The time the UPS will restart in hh:mm format.

upsESystemMasterOffDelay.name: upsESystemMasterOffDelay
upsESystemMasterOffDelay.description: The UPS output will shutdown after the indicated number of seconds, -1 indicate no action.

upsESystemMasterOnDelay.name: upsESystemMasterOnDelay
upsESystemMasterOnDelay.description: The UPS output will start on after the indicated number of seconds, -1 indicate no action.

upsETrapsReceiversTable.name: upsETrapsReceiversTable
upsETrapsReceiversTable.description: This table list the managers'IP to send traps to.

upsETrapsReceiversEntry.name: upsETrapsReceiversEntry
upsETrapsReceiversEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular input line.

upsETrapsReceiversIndex.name: upsETrapsReceiversIndex
upsETrapsReceiversIndex.description: The index to a trap receiver entry

upsETrapsReceiverAddress.name: upsETrapsReceiverAddress
upsETrapsReceiverAddress.description: The IP address of the manager to send a trap to.

upsETrapReceiverCommunityString.name: upsETrapReceiverCommunityString
upsETrapReceiverCommunityString.description: The community name to use in the trap when sent to the manager.

upsETrapType.name: upsETrapType
upsETrapType.description: The type of trap to be received by the manager.

upsETrapsSeverityLevel.name: upsETrapsSeverityLevel
upsETrapsSeverityLevel.description: The severity level of traps to be received by this manager.

upsETrapState.name: upsETrapState
upsETrapState.description: the values indicate the unrestored traps. For example, after AC fail, the agent send the trap 1(AC Fail) and trap 7(battery on) to NMS. so the value of upsETrapState should be '1,7'. And then the AC restore, the value of upsETrapState should change to empty.

upsELowBattery.name: upsELowBattery
upsELowBattery.description: SEVERE: The UPS batteries are low and will soon be exhausted.

upsEReturnFromLowBattery.name: upsEReturnFromLowBattery
upsEReturnFromLowBattery.description: INFORMATION: The UPS has return from a low battery condition.

upsEFailed.name: upsEFailed
upsEFailed.description: SEVERE: The UPS is not working fine.

upsEOk.name: upsEOk
upsEOk.description: INFORMATION: The UPS is working fine.

upsEOnBattery.name: upsEOnBattery
upsEOnBattery.description: WARNING: The UPS has switched to battery backup power.
